      "content": "That's a completely valid perspective, and it often takes a significant amount of trust to believe that seeking professional help won't just add another layer to the cycle you're already stuck in. Sometimes the most effective approach isn't to treat the symptoms or \"fix\" the loop, but to sit with the exhaustion and acknowledge that your resistance to fixing it is actually a form of self-preservation. Perhaps looking for a therapist who specializes in accepting one's pain without trying to immediately resolve it could offer a different kind of support.",
